<subSubSection pageId="2" pageNumber="282" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1437,297,575]" pageId="2" pageNumber="282">
Labels: “Bandaisha/ 
<collectingCountry box="[430,533,369,395]" name="Taiwan" pageId="2" pageNumber="282">Formosa</collectingCountry>
/1, VII, 1965,” “Gen. No./ 66079,” “ 
<taxonomicName authorityName="de Niceville" authorityYear="1890" box="[945,1089,369,395]" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Aeromachus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="282" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Aeromachus</taxonomicName>
/ bandaishanus/ Mur et Shim./ 
<typeStatus box="[151,305,405,431]" pageId="2" pageNumber="282">HOLOTYPE</typeStatus>
.”
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1437,297,575]" pageId="2" pageNumber="282">
A male specimen was designated as the 
<typeStatus box="[658,756,441,467]" pageId="2" pageNumber="282">holotype</typeStatus>
by 
<bibRefCitation author="Murayama, S. &amp; Shimonoya, T." box="[801,1173,441,468]" pageId="2" pageNumber="282" pagination="1 - 16" refId="ref6271" refString="Murayama, S. &amp; Shimonoya, T. (1968) A contribution to taxonomy of the Formosan butterflies, with descriptions of 1 new species, 1 new race, 1 unrecorded species, and 11 new aberrant forms. New Entomologist, 17 (1), 1 - 16. [in Japanese]" type="journal article" year="1968">Murayama &amp; Shimonoya (1968)</bibRefCitation>
, and the specimen was retrieved in the Shimonoya collection (
<figureCitation box="[588,726,477,503]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–18" captionStartId="5.[151,264,1896,1921]" captionTargetBox="[172,1429,181,1871]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[159,1429,181,1871]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 1–18. 1–3. Ampittia matudai Murayama, 1943, holotype; 4–6. Erynnis montanus neomontanus Murayama &amp; Yoshisaka, 1959, holotype; 7–9. Ochlodes siva yuchingkina Murayama &amp; Shimonoya, 1962, holotype; 10–12. Aeromachus bandaishanus Murayama &amp; Shimonoya, 1968, holotype; 13–15. Pseudocoladenia pinsbukana Shimonoya &amp; Murayama, 1976, holotype; 16–18. Polytremis zina taiwana Murayama, 1981, holotype. Scale bar = 1 cm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3990959" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3990959/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="282">Figs. 10–12</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1437,297,575]" pageId="2" pageNumber="282">
Though this species might be related to a continental species such as 
<taxonomicName authority="(Leech, 1890)" baseAuthorityName="Leech" baseAuthorityYear="1890" box="[919,1182,513,539]" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Aeromachus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="282" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nanus">
<emphasis box="[919,1017,513,539]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="282">A. nanus</emphasis>
(Leech, 1890)
</taxonomicName>
, we regard 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Murayama &amp; Shimonoya" authorityYear="1968" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Aeromachus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="282" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bandaishanus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="282">bandaishanus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as a valid species name.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
